concerns: Overall, increases/decreases in all of the categories regarding advancement of function or presence of some of the categories.
improve_format: Could you provide the information in   Table format? It would be easier to compare the periodic info. in the case of the wearable sensor, could you tell us more of what the mPower info reveals?
onesuggestion: Perhaps a Line chart to show progression or changes within a certain assessment.  I realize they are not all direct comparisons across the board.
additional_feedback: How results of this study or others in the University, are providing information to advance toward a cure or better medications.
ghprop_problem: My growing inability to walk due to my posture and advancing PD.
ghprop_bother: I feel discouraged and it really began right after I retired. So, now that we have the time to travel (once COVID restrictions are lifted) I really can't walk and enjoy places.
ghprop_relieve: I have joined a stamina and core building program in my city. Every day I participate in either weight-training, boxing, mat strength building, as well as POLE WALKING which has really helped me to walk longer distances.
ghprop_problem_2: Urinary tract dysfunction. I have a hard time regulating my urinary functions and have had accidents. I also am disturbed almost every night having to get up to empty my bladder.
ghprop_bother_2: I would like to go places without worrying if I'm going to have an accident. It seems I am beginning to reject going places if I can't plan out where I might be able to use the bathroom. And in the case of nighttime, I would like to sleep through the night.
ghprop_relieve_2: I have consulted a Urologist and am taking medication for over-active bladder. It's helping a little but I still wear a Poise pad at night in case of an accident. And as far as going somewhere and planning out the trip around available bathrooms, that still exists.
ghprop_problem_3: Some pain and fatigue in the evening and when rising in the morning.
ghprop_bother_3: In the evening, I am pretty much restricted to making dinner and clean ups and that is it, I'm so tired.
ghprop_relieve_3: The pain has lessened thanks to the exercises I am doing.
ghprop_problem_4: I think about how I'm progressing and am very worried about what I will be like in the future. I have seen a few people I know with PD and they are really compromised. I don't want to be a burden.
ghprop_bother_4: I am trying to "get things in order" like changes to my will and other paperwork. Clean out areas I our home that need attention.
ghprop_relieve_4: I have been doing long term projects like this for about a year.
ghprop_problem_5: Lack of concentration. I have a bunch of projects going at once and am losing my concentration on many of them. I look back on my performance of my job before I retired and I see a lack of concentration and  nervousness.
ghprop_bother_5: It's hard to get things done.
ghprop_relieve_5: Sometimes I do a crossword or other puzzle . It seems to calm me down. Also, breathing exercises.
psprop_problem: My inability to walk is really bothering me.  I feel that this summer will show me how I have changed as compared to last year. I have gardening and activities that I may or may not be able to do. This will show me how I have changed for the good or not.
psprop_bother: As far as walking, I always take a cart in a large store in order to lean on and get around - even if I am buying nothing. I have not advanced to using my walking poles for mobility in the stores because I'm embarrassed to use them. Although I did do so when we were on vacation and it worked ok. As an example however, I tried to walk my dog around Cazenovia yesterday and I thought I was going to die - it's really hard for me to breathe when I walk.
psprop_relieve: I am working with a Physical Therapist who has led our Weight Training, Balance, and Pole Walking classes. She leads a Posture class. We will work together.
psprop_problem_2: Also, I am worried about our finances. Hoping all will be ok if my health gets very bad. I have connected with our attorney and our financial planner to do what we can ahead of time.
psprop_bother_2: There are things I know we should spend our money on investing in our home and I get a little anxious about the constant list of those things. Should we save our money to cover medical bills in our future or invest in our home and other items.
psprop_relieve_2: Ask for advice from our financial planner and attorney. I have done so and we are working with them.
pdprop_problem: My inability to walk is my most bothersome problem.
pdprop_bother: I love to walk and before I was diagnosed with PD I went to various specialists to determine what was wrong with my back. I am very sad to now realize it is an advancing situation from PD.
pdprop_relieve: I am exercising every day to build my strength up.
pdprop_problem_2: The future is a concern to me. I worry about our finances and if I need expensive medical care, how will we afford it.
pdprop_bother_2: It just makes me worry a lot about the future.
pdprop_relieve_2: Talk to our advisors and make a plan.
